y on the impact of tourism on a country that came into being as a tourist destination.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCulture and tourismxBritish Virgin Islands. 0aCulture and tourismzBritish Virgin Islands. 0aNationalismxBritish Virgin Islands. 0aNationalismzBritish Virgin Islands. 0aTourismxBritish Virgin Islands. 0aTourismzBritish Virgin Islands. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311068861040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081355031240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813550312423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780813550312/original  a978-3-11-068861-0  Rutgers University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK